President Trump's imposition of tariffs on foreign steel has led to the rebirth of the Granite City steelworks in St. Louis, along with other steel and aluminum production facilities across the country. The tariffs have resulted in billions of dollars in new investment, increased production, and job creation. Critics argue that the tariffs will raise prices and ultimately cost more jobs, but the impact on prices is minimal and necessary for national security. Furthermore, the low tariffs and non-tariff barriers in the U.S. have led to threats to national security and a significant trade deficit. President Trump's trade policies aim to create a fair and balanced global trade system.